{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01K7nqycPxLSdLcvdYkrpZhc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly:\n\n- **HTTPS (`https://es.example.com`)** returns HTTP 200 with the Elasticsearch response — the API is fully reachable.\n- **Plain HTTP (`http://es.example.com`)** returns HTTP 308 (Permanent Redirect to HTTPS) — the request is rejected/not served as plain HTTP.\n\nHere's what was created:\n\n1. **TLS secret `es-example-com-tls`** (namespace `elasticsearch`) — a self-signed certificate for `es.example.com` generated via the existing `openssl-toolbox` pod.\n\n2. **Ingress `es-ingress`** (namespace `elasticsearch`) with:\n   - `ingressClassName: nginx` — uses the nginx ingress class\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: HTTPS` — tells nginx to proxy to the ES backend over HTTPS (since ES has `xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true`)\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/force-ssl-redirect: \"true\"` — plain HTTP is permanently redirected to HTTPS, never served\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/proxy-ssl-verify: \"off\"` — skips backend cert validation (the ES cert's SANs don't cover the external hostname)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":501,"cache_read_input_tokens":37360,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":501},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"unavailable"}},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7c8f500-1599-4e82-8700-2bbdc9d420b5","uuid":"f2e55bda-e8f8-4a7e-9c86-7ad2996340db","request_id":"req_011Cc9axjJpoYZFsa6nmZGvK"}
